etymologies: late 15th century: from Latin digitalis, from digitus ‘finger, toe’

definitions: (of signals or data) expressed as series of the digits 0 and 1, typically represented by values of a physical quantity such as voltage or magnetic polarization.
shortDefinitions: referring to signals/information represented by discrete values of quantity

definitions: relating to, using, or storing data or information in the form of digital signals
involving or relating to the use of computer technology
(of a clock or watch) showing the time by means of displayed digits rather than hands or a pointer.
shortDefinitions: (of watch) showing time by displayed digits rather than hands

definitions: relating to a finger or fingers.
